b. Acceptance Criteria:

1. User Login
Acceptance Criteria:
User enters a registered email and correct password
System verifies the credentials in the database
User is redirected to the dashboard after successful login
Invalid email or password shows an error message on the same page
Unauthorized users cannot access dashboard pages without logging in

2. Pregnancy Week and Trimester Calculation
Acceptance Criteria:
User enters a valid due date
System calculates the current pregnancy week automatically
System displays the correct trimester based on the calculated week
The displayed pregnancy week updates correctly over time

3. Weekly Pregnancy Tracking Entry
Acceptance Criteria:
User can enter weight, symptoms, and notes
System saves the entry successfully in the database
The same week cannot be entered twice for the same patient
Saved entry appears on the dashboard or tracking page

4. Labour Operation Status Update
Acceptance Criteria:
Doctor or nurse selects the patient record
Doctor or nurse enters the labour stage or operation update
System stores the update with date and time
Family view shows the newest status correctly
Older updates remain visible as a history list

5. Family Monitoring View
Acceptance Criteria:
Family member opens the labour monitoring page
System shows current operation stage
System shows baby status and mother status
Updates appear in the correct order
Page reflects the latest entered information


