a. Architecture
The project follows a three-tier architecture:

Presentation Layer: HTML, CSS, JavaScript pages used by mothers, family members, doctors, nurses, and admin

Business Logic Layer: PHP handles login, pregnancy tracking, labour monitoring, validation, and role-based access

Data Layer: MySQL stores users, pregnancy records, labour monitoring updates, and related data

b. Database Model
Main Tables
Users

Pregnant_Women

Pregnancy_Tracking

Labour_Tracking

Admin

Relationships
One User can have one Pregnant_Woman profile

One Pregnant_Woman can have many Pregnancy_Tracking records

One Pregnant_Woman can have many Labour_Tracking updates

Admin manages records across the system

c. Technologies Used
HTML – structure of pages

CSS – styling and responsive design

JavaScript – interaction and dynamic page behavior

PHP – backend logic and implementation

MySQL – database implementation and storage

d. User Interface Design Summary
Step 1: Login Page
The user sees email and password fields, a login button, and a link to register. If the credentials are wrong, an error message is shown on the same page.

Step 2: Register Page
New users enter their name, email, and password to create an account.

Step 3: Dashboard
After login, the mother sees her pregnancy dashboard with due date, current pregnancy week, trimester, and summary of previous entries.

Step 4: Pregnancy Tracking Page
The mother can add weekly weight, symptoms, and notes. Previous records are also visible.

Step 5: Labour Monitoring Page
During labour, doctors or nurses update the operation stage, mother status, baby status, and notes. Family members can view this progress in a simple and clear monitoring interface.

Step 6: Admin View
The admin sees user and record management sections to control the stored data.

e. Security Measures
Based on our current project structure, the system includes these security measures:

Authentication with email and password during login

Password hashing/encryption before database storage

Session management to keep users logged in securely

Role-based access control for admin, mother, doctor, and nurse views

Input validation before saving data

Prepared statements to reduce SQL Injection risk

XSS protection using safe output methods such as htmlspecialchars()

Secure logout to destroy session data





